            <title>[FLINK-21453] BoundedOneInput.endInput is NOT called when doing stop with savepoint WITH drain</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21453</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21132&quot; title=&quot;BoundedOneInput.endInput is called when taking synchronous savepoint&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-21132&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-21132&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we disable &lt;tt&gt;endInput&lt;/tt&gt; calls when stopping with savepoint. However as discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21133?focusedCommentId=17288467&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-17288467&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;FLINK-21133&lt;/a&gt;, stop with savepoint with drain (&lt;b&gt;stop-with-savepoint --drain&lt;/b&gt;), should be calling &lt;tt&gt;endOfInput()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
